column2: 1. Consists of receipts by all U.S. residents of dividends paid by their incorporated foreign
affiliates and of earnings of their unincorporated foreign affiliates, net of the corresponding
payments.  Estimates for 1929 include reinvested earnings of incorporated affiliates.  For
other years, reinvested earnings are included in undistributed profits in table 6.21A.
Note.  Estimates in this table are based on the 1942 Standard Industrial Classification (SIC).
